    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No, you don't. An Erlenmeyer flask is for general mixing and titration. You do not apply heat to an Erlenmeyer flask. That's what the boiling flask is for. Did you not learn anything in my chemistry class?</Text>
