      <Text>DUPREE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is ••• this is glass grade. You got ••• Jesus, you got crystals in here a quarter-inch long. Longer. This is pure glass.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(turns to him)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You're ••• you're Michelangelo. You're a goddamned artist. This is art. Mr. White •.•</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He's run out of superlatives. He's actually tearing Ye. walt is surprised by his emotion.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
